         Well my updated though.</P><P>I honestly don't give a crap if a level 4 necro can now get more exp with his pet than I ever did.  People complaining about the necro class are level 60, we've been 60 for a long long time.  Where the hell is the improvement for us?</P><P>Is the necromancer a pet class?  I'd say yes because it sure feels like we've been nerfed a lot.  Why do we suffer any exp penalty at all for ever using a pet?  I've DC'd a pet in HS that could nearly match an unbuffed 60 monk's dps.  With my spells I'd have done more.  Is the point of the nerfs to make sure a necro cannot outdamage any class and still get exp?</P><P>Now with dire charm (and I'm sure more than a few have it) we have to basically try to ks our pets everytime.  That defeats the purpose/benefit of having a pet.  People say that having two dire charmed pets on a mob will take that penalty away, I say bullocks.  This is VI, if both pets do more than half together expect less exp.  </P><P>Would a monk/shaman combo suffer the same consequences?  nope. they'd be making twice the exp and still be useful on raids etc.</P><P>Consider this: you dire charm a pet that you've worked hard to get the aa for.  Buff it, then go pull a mob.  Hopefully pet tanks it, so here you go.  Pet is fighting mob, you need to bond mob and pact pet.  Pact again, snare, bond again, maybe dot once.  Mob dies, you're at 90% mana.  Now who did the most damage?  Well the pet did.  VI is saying that what you have done is 25% of the work.  So the pet that you healed, charmed, buffed just took 75% of your exp.</P><P>Shaman/monk: same thing but generally better dps with no downtime each share 50% of the exp.  What did they do?  Shaman slowed, buffed (once every hour), and maybe jbb'd.  Monk hit autoattack and went to the washroom.</P><P>So necro doing 100% of the work gets 25%, other players doing 50% of the work get 50% of the exp.  Or heaven forbid they are doing 100% of the work (like every single melee in FG with a fungi) and getting 100% of the exp.</P><P>Whoever thought this "fix" up is a jerkoff.  You know they don't play a pet class cause this isn't a bonus.</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
